cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with neural image/video captioning models and their internal process of mapping regions to words. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new approach to visual saliency guided by captions, which involves training encoder-decoder networks on caption data. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
